note.ab:
The works exhibited by Charles Degroux were 
                            Franciscus Junius secretly preaching the Reformation at Antwerp
                         (1860); 
                            The drunkard
                         (c. 1853); 
                            The pilgrimage of Saint Guido at Anderlecht
                         (c. 1856-1857); 
                            Saying grace
                         (c. 1860); 
                            The conscript’s departure
                         (c. 1869-1870) and 
                            Head of an old woman
                         (presumably lost or destroyed). See cat. Brussels 1984, pp. 255-258.
